The paper deals with the problem of maximum link scheduling in wireless networks, which is a fundamental problem in the field of networked systems and falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also focuses on developing fast distributed algorithms, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper uses techniques from information theory to develop its algorithms, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the impact of different aspects of available technology on the performance of the algorithm, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and systems and control (cs.SI).
